TITLE: Configuring Proxmox Provider Block in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: Example configuration block showing structure and supported arguments for the Proxmox provider, including authentication options, SSH configuration, and VM ID management settings. Supports various authentication methods including API tokens, username/password, and external auth tickets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bpg/terraform-provider-proxmox/blob/main/docs/index.md#2025-04-23_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
provider "proxmox" {
  endpoint = "https://<your-cluster-endpoint>:8006/"
  insecure = false
  min_tls = "1.3"

  # Authentication (choose one method)
  api_token = "username@realm!for-terraform-provider=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx"
  # or
  username = "root@pam"
  password = "your-password"
  # or
  auth_ticket = "PVE:username@realm:12345678::some_base64_payload=="
  csrf_prevention_token = "12345678:some_blob"

  # SSH Configuration
  ssh {
    username = "ssh-user"
    password = "ssh-password"
    agent = false
    private_key = "path-to-private-key"

    node {
      name = "node1"
      address = "node1.example.com"
      port = 22
    }
  }

  # VM ID Management
  random_vm_ids = false
  random_vm_id_start = 10000
  random_vm_id_end = 99999
}
```

