TITLE: Filtering Proxmox VMs with Multiple Criteria in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use the proxmox_virtual_environment_vms data source with multiple filters to query specific VMs based on tags, template status, VM status, name pattern, and node name pattern.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bpg/terraform-provider-proxmox/blob/main/docs/data-sources/virtual_environment_vms.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
data "proxmox_virtual_environment_vms" "ubuntu_templates" {
  tags      = ["template", "latest"]

  filter {
    name   = "template"
    values = [true]
  }

  filter {
    name   = "status"
    values = ["stopped"]
  }

  filter {
    name   = "name"
    regex  = true
    values = ["^ubuntu-20.*$"]
  }

  filter {
    name   = "node_name"
    regex  = true
    values = ["node_us_[1-3]", "node_eu_[1-3]"]
  }
}
```

